/hpc2hdd/home/xhao390/py/urbanclip/data/: The image captures a panoramic view of a street in Beijing, China. The perspective is from a low angle, looking up towards the sky, giving a sense of grandeur to the scene. The street is lined with power lines and telephone poles, a common sight in many urban areas. Buildings of various sizes and designs flank the street, their facades bathed in the warm glow of the setting sun. The sky above is a clear blue, providing a striking contrast to the earthy tones of the buildings. In the distance, a smattering of trees can be seen, adding a touch of green to the otherwise urban landscape. The image is bathed in the soft light of the setting sun, casting long shadows and highlighting the architectural details of the buildings.
